The paper deals with compressed sensing and noise in measurements, which are topics covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, the focus on linear correlation between signal and measurement noise suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SP (Signal Processing). The use of a linear model and numerical experiments also suggest that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia), while the application to low-rate quantization suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
